cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with object category viewpoint estimation using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a problem related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various design choices and training methods for CNNs, which are related to deep learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of synthetic data and the joint training with the detection task also suggest that cs.RO (Robotics) could be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the Pascal3D+ dataset, which is related to 3D modeling and rendering, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
